    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Ah, I think I know what the issue is. It's probably still constructing the mining DAG. That takes a few minutes and it's multi-threaded, so it will use up all your cores until it finishes. Mining itself will be single threaded afterwards. \r\n\r\nYou can verify by looking at the logs. If it prints something along the lines of `Generating DAG in progress`, it's still building the dataset on multiple threads.",
